13:55.168 --> 13:57.253
PARKER, HARDISON, WE'RE UP.

13:57.295 --> 13:59.339
ELIOT, I NEED THAT UPDATE.

14:00.923 --> 14:02.133
NEXT FERRY DOESN'T LEAVE

14:00.923 --> 14:02.133
TILL THE A.M.

14:02.175 --> 14:03.134
THEY GOT ONE MOTOR BOAT.

14:03.176 --> 14:04.302
THIS THING'S AN ANTIQUE.

14:04.344 --> 14:05.928
IT'S NEVER GONNA MAKE THE TRIP.

14:05.970 --> 14:07.639
Well, that's not acceptable.

14:07.681 --> 14:09.599
WELL, I TOLD YOU I NEEDED A WEEK

14:07.681 --> 14:09.599
TO PREP, DIDN'T I?

14:09.641 --> 14:10.975
Nate, we got a problem.

14:11.017 --> 14:13.269
THIS PLACE ISN'T JUST

14:11.017 --> 14:13.269
OFF THE GRID,

14:13.311 --> 14:15.313
IT'S IN A WHOLE DAMN TIME WARP.

14:17.774 --> 14:19.192
DEFINITELY 1850s.

14:19.233 --> 14:20.568
BEFORE THE CIVIL WAR.

14:20.610 --> 14:22.236
IT'S OLD?

14:20.610 --> 14:22.236
THAT'S  THE PROBLEM?

14:22.278 --> 14:23.613
It's prehistoric.

14:23.655 --> 14:25.615
IT'S TOTALLY ANALOG, ALL MANUAL.

14:25.657 --> 14:28.159
THERE'S A JUNCTION BOX

14:25.657 --> 14:28.159
ON EVERY DAMN FLOOR.

14:28.201 --> 14:30.119
THERE'S NO COMPUTERS,

14:28.201 --> 14:30.119
NOTHING TO CRACK,

14:30.161 --> 14:31.204
NOTHING TO HACK.

14:31.245 --> 14:32.539
[ ELECTRICITY BUZZING ]

14:32.580 --> 14:35.333
AND  THAT  IS ON MY LAST NERVE.

14:35.375 --> 14:36.917
HARDISON, WHAT'S THE RULE?

14:36.959 --> 14:40.296
DON'T BRING UP A PROBLEM

14:36.959 --> 14:40.296
UNLESS YOU GOT A FIX.

14:40.338 --> 14:41.631
OKAY, FINE. WHATEVER.

14:41.673 --> 14:45.051
UM, OH. YOU KNOW WHAT?

14:41.673 --> 14:45.051
UH, MAYBE...

14:45.092 --> 14:48.555
WITH WHAT I GOT HERE,

14:45.092 --> 14:48.555
I CAN MAKE A PULSE MAP.

14:48.596 --> 14:50.473
-I'M SORRY -- A  WHAT?

14:48.596 --> 14:50.473
-A pulse map.

14:50.515 --> 14:52.517
I TAKE MY GEAR,

14:50.515 --> 14:52.517
ATTACH IT TO THE WIRING,

14:52.559 --> 14:55.269
SEE WHAT DRAWS THE MOST POWER

14:52.559 --> 14:55.269
BY SENDING OUT SOME PULSES.

14:55.311 --> 14:57.605
MAYBE WE CAN FIND

14:55.311 --> 14:57.605
THE MAIN CONTROL ROOM.

14:57.647 --> 14:59.106
Yeah, or anything big,

14:59.148 --> 15:01.776
like a state-of-the-art safe

14:59.148 --> 15:01.776
filled with blueprints.

15:01.818 --> 15:04.529
EITHER WAY PUTS US

15:01.818 --> 15:04.529
BACK IN BUSINESS.

15:04.571 --> 15:06.322
Well, see?

15:04.571 --> 15:06.322
Problem, solution.

15:06.364 --> 15:08.366
THIS PLACE IS

15:06.364 --> 15:08.366
FRIGGIN' GINORMOUS.

15:08.408 --> 15:09.868
IT'S GONNA TAKE ME A WHILE.

15:09.909 --> 15:11.911
THEN I SUGGEST YOU GET ON IT.

15:11.952 --> 15:13.913
HE'S GOT TO BE TELLING

15:11.952 --> 15:13.913
SOMEBODY WHAT TO DO --

15:13.954 --> 15:15.039
"GET TO IT."

15:15.081 --> 15:17.417
OH, THAT'S FUNNY.

15:17.458 --> 15:20.169
HE DOESN'T EVEN KNOW

15:17.458 --> 15:20.169
WHAT A PULSE MAP IS.

15:20.211 --> 15:22.422
OKAY, OKAY,

15:20.211 --> 15:22.422
TWO FLOORS DOWN, EAST CORNER.

15:22.463 --> 15:23.964
PARKER, YOU'RE ON.

15:22.463 --> 15:23.964
GO, GO, GO!

15:24.006 --> 15:26.050
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

15:32.056 --> 15:34.267
[ GASPS ]

15:34.308 --> 15:35.976
HEY, GET OUT!

15:36.018 --> 15:39.898
OR JOIN IN.

15:36.018 --> 15:39.898
[ GIGGLES ]

15:43.401 --> 15:46.237
NO SAFE -- JUST A GIANT PANTRY

15:43.401 --> 15:46.237
WITH THE MASTER SWITCH BOX

15:46.279 --> 15:48.030
AND BECK'S SWEATY DAUGHTER

15:46.279 --> 15:48.030
IN IT.

15:48.072 --> 15:49.532
NEXT.

15:49.574 --> 15:52.993
OKAY, HOLD ON.

15:49.574 --> 15:52.993
HOLD ON, HOLD ON.

15:53.035 --> 15:54.203
[ BEEPING ]

15:54.245 --> 15:56.289
GOT YOU. REAR OF THE HOUSE.

15:54.245 --> 15:56.289
SECOND FLOOR.

15:56.330 --> 15:57.707
I'LL TAKE THAT ONE.

15:57.749 --> 16:00.126
NO, W-WAIT. YOU PUT ME

15:57.749 --> 16:00.126
AND PARKER ON THE SAFE SEARCH.

16:00.167 --> 16:02.211
I'M CLOSER.

16:00.167 --> 16:02.211
I'LL TAKE IT.

16:02.253 --> 16:05.548
HEY, ATTENTION.

16:02.253 --> 16:05.548
UP HERE. HEY!

16:05.590 --> 16:07.091
[ WHISTLES ]

16:07.133 --> 16:09.009
THANK YOU.

16:09.051 --> 16:13.264
AFTER LAST YEAR'S [SIGHS]

16:09.051 --> 16:13.264
HUMAN CHESS FIASCO,

16:13.306 --> 16:15.099
THERE WERE A LOT OF SORE LOSERS.

16:15.141 --> 16:16.559
WELL, THERE ALWAYS ARE.

16:16.601 --> 16:19.103
BUT I DON'T WANT YOU DIMWITS

16:16.601 --> 16:19.103
TO THINK

16:19.145 --> 16:21.564
THAT I DON'T GIVE YOU

16:19.145 --> 16:21.564
A FAIR SHAKE.

16:21.606 --> 16:22.982
TONIGHT'S CHALLENGE

16:23.023 --> 16:25.985
IS A MURDER MYSTERY.

16:26.026 --> 16:28.195
AT THE STROKE OF MIDNIGHT,

16:28.237 --> 16:30.907
SOMEONE  WILL DIE.

16:30.949 --> 16:32.575
AND ONE OF YOU IS THE KILLER.

16:32.617 --> 16:34.118
WHOEVER SOLVES THE MURDER

16:34.160 --> 16:37.204
BY DAWN WILL RECEIVE A CHECK

16:37.246 --> 16:39.499
FOR $100,000.

16:39.540 --> 16:41.083
HEY. COME BACK HERE!

16:41.125 --> 16:43.002
[ CROWD MURMURING ]

16:43.043 --> 16:45.922
JUST MAKE IT INTERESTING...

16:45.964 --> 16:47.381
FOR ONCE.

16:47.423 --> 16:48.883
[ THUNDER CRASHES ]

16:47.423 --> 16:48.883
-PLEASE.

16:48.925 --> 16:50.927
[ GRUNTING ]

16:53.137 --> 16:55.097
[ THUD ]

16:56.140 --> 16:57.224
[ SCREAMS ]

16:57.266 --> 16:58.768
[ PEOPLE MURMURING ]

16:58.810 --> 17:02.271
OH, MY GOD!

17:02.313 --> 17:03.439
HE KILLED DADDY!

17:11.572 --> 17:13.616
[ HAYLEY SCREAMS ]

17:13.658 --> 17:15.242
OH, MY GOD!

17:15.284 --> 17:16.327
HE KILLED DADDY!

17:17.662 --> 17:19.246
[ Normal voice ]

17:17.662 --> 17:19.246
NO, EVERYBODY --

17:19.288 --> 17:20.414
EVERYBODY STAY WHERE YOU ARE.

17:20.456 --> 17:22.959
EVERYBODY JUST -- JUST --

17:20.456 --> 17:22.959
JUST STAY CALM.

17:23.001 --> 17:24.126
STAY CALM?!

17:24.168 --> 17:25.211
HE JUST MURDERED MY FATHER!

17:25.252 --> 17:26.379
POTTER, CALL SECURITY!

17:26.420 --> 17:28.464
NO, NO, NO.

17:26.420 --> 17:28.464
NO, THAT WON'T BE NECESSARY.

17:28.506 --> 17:29.423
NO.

17:29.465 --> 17:32.510
THAT'S NOT NECESSARY, BECAUSE...

17:32.552 --> 17:35.638
BECAUSE...

17:35.680 --> 17:39.350
THIS  IS THE CHALLENGE!

17:39.392 --> 17:41.686
THE MYSTERY HAS BEGUN.

17:41.728 --> 17:42.854
NO, IT HASN'T.

17:42.896 --> 17:44.397
THE VICTIM IS STILL ALIVE.

17:44.438 --> 17:46.900
UH, W-WELL, YEAH.

17:44.438 --> 17:46.900
I MEAN, I WAS HIRED TO --

17:46.941 --> 17:49.068
OH, SILLY. [ GIGGLES ]

17:49.109 --> 17:52.446
THIS IS NOT MORRIS BECK.

17:49.109 --> 17:52.446
NO!

17:52.488 --> 17:53.990
THIS IS A DUMMY!

17:54.032 --> 17:55.408
MORRIS BECK

17:55.449 --> 18:00.329
IS SOMEWHERE IN THE HOUSE,

17:55.449 --> 18:00.329
WATCHING ALL OF YOU.

18:00.371 --> 18:02.164
BUT I SPENT HOURS

18:00.371 --> 18:02.164
HIDING THE CLUES.

18:02.206 --> 18:04.834
DO YOU KNOW HOW LONG IT TOOK ME

18:02.206 --> 18:04.834
TO HIDE THAT PIPE WRENCH

18:04.876 --> 18:05.835
IN THE LIBRARY?

18:05.877 --> 18:07.837
ALL PART OF THE SMOKE SCREEN.

18:07.879 --> 18:09.714
MR. BECK KNEW

18:07.879 --> 18:09.714
THAT YOU'D ALL THINK

18:09.756 --> 18:12.091
A SIMPLE MURDER-MYSTERY PARTY

18:09.756 --> 18:12.091
WOULD BE OLD HAT.

18:12.132 --> 18:14.928
HE WANTED SOMETHING FRESH,

18:12.132 --> 18:14.928
SOMETHING EXCITING.

18:14.969 --> 18:16.596
MARK MY WORDS!

18:16.637 --> 18:20.182
SOMEBODY HERE...IS THE KILLER.

18:20.224 --> 18:25.563
NO ONE IS LEAVING

18:20.224 --> 18:25.563
UNTIL WE FIND OUT WHO.

18:25.605 --> 18:27.231
BUT WE ALL JUST SAW THAT MAN.

18:28.274 --> 18:31.277
[ LAUGHS, SIGHS ]

18:31.318 --> 18:32.361
I'M A DOCTOR.

18:32.403 --> 18:33.988
AT LEAST LET ME EXAMINE

18:32.403 --> 18:33.988
THE BODY!

18:34.030 --> 18:35.949
NO, NO, NO!

18:34.030 --> 18:35.949
NOBODY TOUCH THE BODY!

18:35.990 --> 18:38.576
NO, NO. BACK UP. BACK UP.

18:35.990 --> 18:38.576
INSTANT DISQUALIFICATION.

18:38.618 --> 18:41.621
EVERYBODY, MY PARTNER,

18:38.618 --> 18:41.621
MR. GORDON,

18:41.662 --> 18:44.248
OF MYSTERY, INC.

18:44.290 --> 18:45.959
HELLO. HELLO.

18:44.290 --> 18:45.959
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:46.000 --> 18:47.585
OH, SO LIFELIKE.

18:47.627 --> 18:49.921
YES.

18:47.627 --> 18:49.921
IT COST US A FORTUNE.

18:49.963 --> 18:52.256
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

18:52.298 --> 18:54.383
THIS IS PREPOSTEROUS.

18:54.425 --> 18:56.636
MR. BECK WOULD HAVE INFORMED ME

18:54.425 --> 18:56.636
OF ANY CHANGES IN THE EVENING --

18:56.677 --> 18:59.305
AH! AND CHEAT YOU

18:56.677 --> 18:59.305
OF YOUR CHANCE AT THE PRIZE?

18:59.346 --> 19:02.391
YOU'RE A CONTESTANT, TOO.

19:02.433 --> 19:03.517
I-I AM?

19:03.559 --> 19:04.393
YES!

19:04.435 --> 19:05.645
YOU ALL ARE.

19:05.686 --> 19:06.813
REMEMBER --

19:06.854 --> 19:09.983
SOMEBODY HERE COMMITTED

19:06.854 --> 19:09.983
THIS CRIME,

19:10.024 --> 19:12.234
AND SOMEBODY HERE

19:12.276 --> 19:14.445
CAN SOLVE THIS MURDER

19:14.487 --> 19:17.323
FOR $100,000!

19:17.364 --> 19:21.077
AH! A COLLEAGUE!

19:17.364 --> 19:21.077
THE CRIME DOCTOR.

19:21.119 --> 19:22.578
[ Chuckling ] YES.

19:22.620 --> 19:23.913
YES, TAKE A BOW.

19:23.955 --> 19:27.541
NOW, WHAT HE'S GONNA DO NOW

19:23.955 --> 19:27.541
IS HE IS GOING TO...

19:27.583 --> 19:30.044
EXAMINE THE BODY...

19:30.086 --> 19:33.547
AND THEN RETURN WITH MORE CLUES.

19:34.924 --> 19:37.343
YEAH.

19:40.471 --> 19:41.722
GENTLEMEN...

19:41.764 --> 19:43.516
[ SIGHS ]

19:43.557 --> 19:45.643
Good luck.

19:49.396 --> 19:50.940
GOOD, EXCELLENT.

19:50.982 --> 19:53.526
WHILST MR. GORDON

19:50.982 --> 19:53.526
AND THE CRIME DOCTOR

19:53.567 --> 19:55.361
EXAMINE THE BODY,

19:55.402 --> 19:58.114
I SHALL MOVE AMONGST YOU

19:55.402 --> 19:58.114
AND SEE WHO REMEMBERS WHAT.

19:58.156 --> 20:01.784
REMEMBER -- ANYONE HERE

19:58.156 --> 20:01.784
COULD BE THE KILLER.

20:01.826 --> 20:02.869
EVEN YOU?

20:04.328 --> 20:06.288
[ LAUGHS ]

20:06.330 --> 20:10.250
ANYONE,

20:06.330 --> 20:10.250
DETECTIVE RAY HAMMETT.

20:10.292 --> 20:11.919
HE'S A REAL-LIFE DETECTIVE

20:11.961 --> 20:13.921
FROM THE SALEM

20:11.961 --> 20:13.921
POLICE DEPARTMENT.

20:13.963 --> 20:16.256
MIND IF I CONSIDER YOU

20:13.963 --> 20:16.256
A RESOURCE, RAY?

20:16.298 --> 20:18.217
WHY NOT?

20:16.298 --> 20:18.217
NICE ACCENT, BY THE WAY.

20:18.258 --> 20:20.678
ISN'T IT?

20:18.258 --> 20:20.678
AND THIS ONE'S  REAL.

20:20.720 --> 20:23.181
HELP ME LOOK AFTER THIS LOT,

20:23.222 --> 20:25.016
AND THERE'S ANOTHER DANCE

20:23.222 --> 20:25.016
IN IT FOR YOU.

20:25.058 --> 20:26.934
WELL, HOW COULD I

20:25.058 --> 20:26.934
SAY NO TO THAT?

20:26.976 --> 20:28.644
MYSTERY, INC., HUH?

20:28.686 --> 20:30.980
I'M AN ACTRESS.

20:28.686 --> 20:30.980
IT'S A LIVING.

20:31.022 --> 20:32.106
LET'S MINGLE.

20:32.148 --> 20:35.026
WORK, WORK, WORK.

20:44.535 --> 20:46.495
[ SNIFFS ]

20:46.537 --> 20:48.706
YEAH.

20:50.708 --> 20:52.626
-WORK...

20:50.708 --> 20:52.626
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING ]

20:52.668 --> 20:55.379
WORK, WORK.

20:59.008 --> 21:01.844
OKAY, HERE, HERE.

21:01.886 --> 21:03.262
[ CLATTER ]

21:06.557 --> 21:08.642
Wait, wait. What the hell's

21:06.557 --> 21:08.642
going on down there?

21:08.684 --> 21:09.894
NATE  KILLED  SOMEBODY?

21:09.936 --> 21:12.521
NO, NATE DIDN'T KILL SOMEBODY.

21:12.563 --> 21:14.190
-YOU  DIDN'T,  DID YOU?

21:12.563 --> 21:14.190
-OF COURSE NOT.

21:14.232 --> 21:16.734
YOU'D TELL US, THOUGH.

21:16.776 --> 21:18.194
Wouldn't you?

21:18.236 --> 21:20.238
YES, PARKER, I WOULD TELL YOU

21:18.236 --> 21:20.238
IF I MURDERED THE MARK.

21:22.240 --> 21:24.909
BUT HE IS DEAD, THOUGH, RIGHT?

21:22.240 --> 21:24.909
I MEAN, BECK IS DEAD?

21:24.951 --> 21:25.993
YEAH, HE'S DEAD.

21:26.035 --> 21:27.578
SOMEBODY SNAPPED HIS NECK.

21:27.620 --> 21:29.455
-SO IT WASN'T THE FALL?

21:27.620 --> 21:29.455
-UNH-UNH.

21:29.496 --> 21:30.915
THAT WOULDN'T HAPPEN ON IMPACT.

21:29.496 --> 21:30.915
IT'S RADIAL.

21:30.957 --> 21:33.042
IT'S ALL TORQUE.

21:33.084 --> 21:34.794
HE WAS DEAD

21:33.084 --> 21:34.794
BEFORE HE HIT THE GROUND.

21:34.835 --> 21:37.671
WHY?

21:37.713 --> 21:39.924
I MEAN, WHAT POSSIBLE GAIN

21:37.713 --> 21:39.924
WOULD HE HAVE

21:39.966 --> 21:41.550
BY DOING IT NOW,

21:39.966 --> 21:41.550
IN FRONT OF ALL THOSE WITNESSES?

21:41.592 --> 21:43.094
I MEAN,

21:41.592 --> 21:43.094
WHAT'S THAT ABOUT?

21:43.136 --> 21:45.345
YOU'RE CLAIMING SOMEONE ELSE

21:43.136 --> 21:45.345
WAS ON THE BALCONY?

21:45.387 --> 21:48.474
YEAH, 'CAUSE I --

21:45.387 --> 21:48.474
WHAT DO YOU MEAN "CLAIMING"?

21:48.515 --> 21:50.935
GUYS, HERE'S HOW

21:48.515 --> 21:50.935
WE'RE GONNA PLAY THIS.

21:50.977 --> 21:54.272
HARDISON, PARKER, I WANT YOU

21:50.977 --> 21:54.272
TO KEEP SEARCHING FOR THE SAFE.

21:54.313 --> 21:56.232
SOPHIE,

21:54.313 --> 21:56.232
YOU'RE ON CROWD CONTROL.

21:56.274 --> 21:58.651
NO ONE LEAVES THE BALLROOM

21:56.274 --> 21:58.651
UNTIL WE SECURE THE BLUEPRINTS.

21:58.692 --> 22:00.278
ELIOT WILL --

22:00.319 --> 22:02.738
ELIOT'S, WHAT, ELIOT GONNA BUST

22:00.319 --> 22:02.738
YOUR ASS OUT OF JAIL -- AGAIN?

22:02.780 --> 22:05.699
LISTEN, NOTHING'S CHANGED.

22:02.780 --> 22:05.699
WE STILL HAVE A JOB TO DO.

22:05.741 --> 22:06.951
SCREW THE JOB, NATE!

22:06.993 --> 22:08.744
THIS GUY'S DEAD.

22:06.993 --> 22:08.744
SOMEBODY KILLED HIM.

22:08.786 --> 22:11.080
PRETTY SOON, FOLKS ARE GONNA

22:08.786 --> 22:11.080
START ASKING QUESTIONS.

22:11.122 --> 22:13.166
THERE WAS OVER A HUNDRED PEOPLE

22:11.122 --> 22:13.166
AT THAT PARTY,

22:13.207 --> 22:15.251
INCLUDING A COP,

22:13.207 --> 22:15.251
WHO, BY THE WAY, SAW YOU.

22:15.293 --> 22:17.003
YOUR FINGERPRINTS

22:15.293 --> 22:17.003
ARE ALL OVER THIS.

22:17.044 --> 22:18.171
AND YOUR POINT IS?

22:18.212 --> 22:20.298
THE POINT IS...

22:20.339 --> 22:24.593
IF WE DON'T SOLVE THIS MURDER,

22:20.339 --> 22:24.593
YOU'RE COOKED.

22:24.635 --> 22:26.179
YOU GET THAT?

22:26.220 --> 22:28.806
YEAH.

22:26.220 --> 22:28.806
I GET THAT.

22:28.848 --> 22:30.683
OKAY.

22:28.848 --> 22:30.683
THEN FORGET THE JOB.

22:30.724 --> 22:31.767
FORGET THE BLUEPRINTS.

22:31.809 --> 22:33.435
IF YOU DIDN'T KILL THIS GUY --

22:33.477 --> 22:34.603
"IF"?

22:34.645 --> 22:36.105
IF  YOU DIDN'T KILL THIS GUY,

22:36.147 --> 22:37.982
THEN YOU'RE THE ONLY WITNESS.

22:38.024 --> 22:40.901
YOU BETTER SOLVE

22:38.024 --> 22:40.901
THIS MURDER, NATE.

22:40.943 --> 22:42.486
OR?

22:42.528 --> 22:46.448
OR YOU'RE GONNA TAKE THE FALL.

22:53.164 --> 22:56.583
[ THUNDER RUMBLES ]

22:56.625 --> 22:57.793
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

22:57.835 --> 23:00.129
OPEN UP!

22:57.835 --> 23:00.129
SALEM P.D.

23:03.674 --> 23:05.051
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

23:07.053 --> 23:08.054
-YEAH?

23:07.053 --> 23:08.054
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

23:08.095 --> 23:09.972
HAMMETT.

23:08.095 --> 23:09.972
DETECTIVE HAMMETT?

23:10.014 --> 23:11.473
I NEED TO SEE MR. BECK.

23:11.515 --> 23:13.184
SORRY. NO CAN DO.

23:13.226 --> 23:15.644
WHAT PART OF "DETECTIVE HAMMETT"

23:13.226 --> 23:15.644
AREN'T YOU GETTING, PAL?

23:15.686 --> 23:17.230
WELL, HE'S NOT HERE.

23:17.271 --> 23:19.565
AND HE TOLD US NOT TO TELL

23:17.271 --> 23:19.565
ANYBODY  WHERE HE WAS.

23:19.606 --> 23:20.858
AND HE PAYS THE BILLS.

23:20.900 --> 23:22.776
[ GASPS ]

23:20.900 --> 23:22.776
THERE YOU ARE.

23:22.818 --> 23:24.028
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

23:24.070 --> 23:25.238
I NEED YOU TO COME

23:24.070 --> 23:25.238
TO THE BALLROOM WITH ME,

23:25.279 --> 23:26.239
IF YOU DON'T MIND.

23:26.280 --> 23:27.489
-LISTEN, MISS SUMAC --

23:26.280 --> 23:27.489
-YMA.

23:27.531 --> 23:28.615
-YMA.

23:28.657 --> 23:30.368
I NEED YOU TO COME WITH ME,

23:28.657 --> 23:30.368
DETECTIVE.

23:30.408 --> 23:33.871
ONE OF THE "GUESTS"

23:30.408 --> 23:33.871
HAS SOME INFORMATION FOR YOU.

23:37.708 --> 23:39.085
Good work, Sophie.

23:39.126 --> 23:42.546
KEEP HIM BUSY

23:39.126 --> 23:42.546
TILL WE GET THROUGH THIS.

23:43.714 --> 23:45.007
ALL RIGHT, ONE GOOD THING.

23:45.049 --> 23:46.175
[ LOCK CLICKS ]

23:46.217 --> 23:47.968
KILLER'S GOT

23:46.217 --> 23:47.968
THE SAME PROBLEM WE DO --

23:48.010 --> 23:49.845
NO WAY OFF THE ISLAND

23:48.010 --> 23:49.845
TILL THE MORNING.

23:49.887 --> 23:52.806
NATE?

23:52.848 --> 23:54.474
CAN YOU HEAR ME?

23:56.977 --> 23:58.645
[ THUNDER RUMBLES ]

23:58.687 --> 24:00.564
[ GRUNTING ]

24:03.901 --> 24:05.069
[ GROANING ]

24:05.111 --> 24:08.488
ELIOT, I NEED YOU TO HELP ME

24:05.111 --> 24:08.488
FIND THE KILLER.

24:08.530 --> 24:11.242
AND HOW DO I DO THAT, EXACTLY?

24:13.493 --> 24:15.079
THIS IS A BAD IDEA.

24:15.121 --> 24:17.206
THE WAY I GET INFORMATION OUT OF

24:15.121 --> 24:17.206
GUYS IS USUALLY LOUD AND MESSY.

24:17.248 --> 24:19.875
TONIGHT YOU'RE A GRIFTER.

24:17.248 --> 24:19.875
ADAPT.

24:19.917 --> 24:21.001
YEAH, WHEN THIS IS OVER,

24:21.043 --> 24:22.753
ME AND YOU ARE GONNA HAVE

24:21.043 --> 24:22.753
A LITTLE TALK.

24:22.795 --> 24:24.255
JUST TELL ME

24:22.795 --> 24:24.255
WHAT HE LOOKS LIKE.

24:24.297 --> 24:27.216
Medium build,

24:24.297 --> 24:27.216
dark jacket, short hair.

24:29.176 --> 24:30.468
BINGO.

24:33.389 --> 24:36.183
[ GRUNTING ]

24:37.768 --> 24:41.730
NOW, I WANT YOU TO CHECK

24:37.768 --> 24:41.730
HIS INSIDE JACKET POCKET

24:41.772 --> 24:43.607
FOR SOMETHING SHINY.

24:43.649 --> 24:45.359
EXCUSE ME.

24:45.401 --> 24:47.569
YEAH.

24:47.611 --> 24:49.238
YOU'RE CAPRIOTTI, RIGHT?

24:49.280 --> 24:51.740
WHAT'S IT TO YOU?

24:51.782 --> 24:54.618
YOU MET MISS SUMAC.

24:51.782 --> 24:54.618
CORRECT?

24:54.660 --> 24:56.620
THE FOREIGN CHICK?

24:56.662 --> 24:57.704
NICE RACK.

24:57.746 --> 25:01.417
THE WAY YOU PUT YOUR HANDS

24:57.746 --> 25:01.417
ON HER,

25:01.459 --> 25:03.752
THAT DOESN'T HAPPEN

25:01.459 --> 25:03.752
IF I'M IN HERE.

25:03.794 --> 25:06.213
THAT A FACT?

25:06.255 --> 25:07.340
ELIOT, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

25:07.381 --> 25:08.548
THAT'S FUNNY.

25:08.590 --> 25:10.550
'CAUSE I WAS THINKING

25:10.592 --> 25:13.387
ABOUT PUTTING MY HANDS

25:10.592 --> 25:13.387
ON HER  AGAIN.

25:13.429 --> 25:14.763
REAL FRIENDLY LIKE.

25:14.805 --> 25:18.642
GOT SOMETHING TO SAY ABOUT IT...

25:18.684 --> 25:20.144
COWGIRL?

25:20.186 --> 25:21.812
YEAH.

25:23.314 --> 25:25.983
[ GROANS ]

25:28.235 --> 25:30.029
IT'S A FLASK.

25:30.070 --> 25:31.947
IT'S ALL --

25:30.070 --> 25:31.947
IT'S ALL PART OF THE SHOW.

25:31.989 --> 25:33.199
[ CHUCKLES ]

25:33.240 --> 25:34.992
HOW YOU DOING?

25:33.240 --> 25:34.992
GOOD SPORT, THERE.

25:35.034 --> 25:37.077
THANK YOU.

25:35.034 --> 25:37.077
IS THAT THE GUY?

25:37.119 --> 25:38.412
I DON'T KNOW.

25:38.454 --> 25:41.332
CAPRIOTTI -- HE HATED BECK

25:38.454 --> 25:41.332
FOR CHEATING THE UNIONS.

25:41.374 --> 25:42.708
HE THREATENED HIM...

25:42.749 --> 25:43.709
I DON'T KNOW.

25:43.750 --> 25:45.461
I DON'T KNOW.

25:43.750 --> 25:45.461
IT'S NOT ENOUGH.

25:45.503 --> 25:46.962
[ SIGHS ]

25:47.004 --> 25:48.630
WE CAN'T ELIMINATE HIM,

25:48.672 --> 25:52.092
BUT I WOULD BET ON SOMEONE

25:48.672 --> 25:52.092
WHO KNEW BECK BETTER,

25:52.134 --> 25:55.095
SOMEONE WHO HAD A PERSONAL BEEF

25:52.134 --> 25:55.095
WITH HIM.

25:55.137 --> 25:57.597
LIKE A CO-WORKER?

25:57.639 --> 25:59.517
Try not to assault this one,

25:57.639 --> 25:59.517
Eliot.

25:59.557 --> 26:03.020
MESSY AND LOUD, NATE.

25:59.557 --> 26:03.020
I TOLD YOU -- ADAPT.

26:04.813 --> 26:05.814
DAMN BLACKOUT.

26:05.856 --> 26:07.607
PREHISTORIC WIRE MONSTERS.

26:07.649 --> 26:08.775
NATE'S KILLING FOLKS.

26:08.817 --> 26:10.069
I DID NOT SIGN UP FOR THIS.

26:10.110 --> 26:12.488
NATE DIDN'T KILL ANYONE.

26:10.110 --> 26:12.488
HE SAID.

26:12.530 --> 26:14.572
STILL, WELL...

26:14.614 --> 26:16.658
I HATE THIS HOUSE.

26:16.700 --> 26:18.660
THIS PLACE REMINDS ME

26:16.700 --> 26:18.660
OF MY FIRST GRAB.

26:18.702 --> 26:20.620
SOME LADY'S HOUSE

26:18.702 --> 26:20.620
IN THE PHILIPPINES --

26:20.662 --> 26:21.705
IT WAS LIKE A PALACE.

26:21.747 --> 26:25.000
SHE HAD ALL THESE SHOES.

26:25.042 --> 26:26.626
THESE ARE

26:25.042 --> 26:26.626
THE LAST TWO BOXES, MAN.

26:26.668 --> 26:28.212
THEY DON'T HIT,

26:26.668 --> 26:28.212
WE OUT OF OPTIONS.

26:28.254 --> 26:29.838
THERE'S SOMETHING WEIRD

26:28.254 --> 26:29.838
ABOUT THESE HALLWAYS.

26:29.880 --> 26:31.298
WEIRD? WHAT?

26:29.880 --> 26:31.298
WAIT -- WEIRD, HOW?

26:31.340 --> 26:32.883
IT'S LIKE THE DIMENSIONS

26:31.340 --> 26:32.883
ARE OFF.

26:32.925 --> 26:35.635
WHAT YOU MEAN,

26:32.925 --> 26:35.635
THE DIMENSIONS? WHAT?

26:35.677 --> 26:37.263
YEAH, DO YOU GET THAT THING,

26:37.304 --> 26:39.806
YOU KNOW, WHEN PEOPLE FREAK OUT

26:37.304 --> 26:39.806
IN TIGHT SPACES?

26:39.848 --> 26:41.016
-CLAUSTROPHOBIA?

26:39.848 --> 26:41.016
-MM.

26:41.058 --> 26:43.060
NO. [ CHUCKLES ]

26:43.102 --> 26:44.811
BABY GIRL, IF THERE'S ANYBODY

26:44.853 --> 26:47.731
WHO DOESN'T NEED TO WORRY

26:44.853 --> 26:47.731
ABOUT CLAUSTROPHOBIA, IT'S Y--

26:48.774 --> 26:51.026
UH...HELLO?

26:52.861 --> 26:54.654
PAR--

26:54.696 --> 26:57.699
WOMAN?

26:57.741 --> 27:01.495
PEOPLE, I LOST PARKER.

27:05.416 --> 27:08.085
DAMN IT, NATE,

27:05.416 --> 27:08.085
SHE'S NOT ON COMMS. PARKER?

27:08.127 --> 27:09.795
ELIOT WILL FIND HER.

27:08.127 --> 27:09.795
THAT'S HIS JOB.

27:09.836 --> 27:12.005
Your job is finding the safe.

27:12.047 --> 27:14.425
PARKER!

27:12.047 --> 27:14.425
COME ON, GIRL!

27:14.467 --> 27:15.801
SOMEBODY BETTER DO SOMETHING.

27:15.842 --> 27:17.261
IF THIS DOESN'T GO WELL,

27:15.842 --> 27:17.261
WE COULD ALL LOSE OUR JOBS,

27:17.303 --> 27:19.388
AND MR. BECK,

27:17.303 --> 27:19.388
HE WAS VERY EXPLICIT --

27:19.430 --> 27:20.556
LISTEN, MISS SUMAC --

27:20.598 --> 27:21.932
NO -- OH, PLEASE.

27:20.598 --> 27:21.932
"YMA."

27:21.974 --> 27:24.268
YMA.

27:24.310 --> 27:26.979
ALL RIGHT,

27:24.310 --> 27:26.979
I'M GOING TO LEVEL WITH YOU.

27:27.020 --> 27:28.439
I THINK BECK IS DEAD.

27:28.481 --> 27:31.108
NO, NO, NO. THIS IS ALL

27:28.481 --> 27:31.108
JUST PART OF THE GAME.

27:31.150 --> 27:33.277
THEN EXPLAIN TO ME

27:31.150 --> 27:33.277
WHY I FOUND BLOOD --

27:33.319 --> 27:36.738
REAL BLOOD --

27:33.319 --> 27:36.738
ON THE FLOOR WHERE HE FELL.

27:36.780 --> 27:39.241
[ THUNDER CRASHES ]

27:36.780 --> 27:39.241
-[ GASPS ]

27:39.283 --> 27:41.076
OH, MY GOD.

27:41.118 --> 27:43.203
YOU ACTUALLY THINK

27:41.118 --> 27:43.203
HE MIGHT BE DEAD.

27:43.245 --> 27:45.414
I DON'T KNOW.

27:43.245 --> 27:45.414
I KNOW SOMETHING'S WRONG.

27:45.456 --> 27:47.249
I'M GONNA FIGURE OUT WHAT IT IS.

27:47.291 --> 27:49.876
LOOK, I NEED YOU TO STAY CLOSE.

27:49.918 --> 27:52.921
BECAUSE IF THIS THING

27:49.918 --> 27:52.921
GOES BAD...

27:52.963 --> 27:55.090
I WANT YOU OUT OF HARM'S WAY.

27:55.132 --> 27:58.385
OKAY, RAY.

27:55.132 --> 27:58.385
WHATEVER YOU SAY.

28:00.638 --> 28:01.847
HEAR THAT, NATE?

28:01.888 --> 28:03.849
Case fits the description.

28:03.890 --> 28:06.268
Go check his pocket.

28:06.310 --> 28:08.437
[ SIGHS ]

28:08.479 --> 28:10.022
BOY, THAT BECK.

28:10.063 --> 28:11.731
HE LIKES TO MAKE PEOPLE SWEAT,

28:10.063 --> 28:11.731
DOESN'T HE?

28:11.773 --> 28:15.110
SWITCHING THE EVENING'S EVENTS

28:11.773 --> 28:15.110
WITHOUT NOTIFYING ME?

28:15.152 --> 28:16.445
[ SCOFFS ]

28:16.487 --> 28:17.904
THE MAN'S A TOTAL ASS.

28:17.946 --> 28:20.199
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

28:20.240 --> 28:21.200
I NEED A DRINK.

28:21.241 --> 28:22.201
SO DO I.

28:22.242 --> 28:23.452
WANT TO JOIN ME?

28:23.494 --> 28:24.453
YES, PLEASE.

28:24.495 --> 28:25.496
ALL RIGHT.

28:27.705 --> 28:29.583
SORRY.

28:29.625 --> 28:31.793
I GOT IT. SMARTPHONE?

28:31.835 --> 28:34.421
NO.

28:34.463 --> 28:35.755
I MEAN, MAYBE.

28:35.797 --> 28:37.757
CASE WAS ON THE FLOOR

28:35.797 --> 28:37.757
ASKING QUESTIONS.

28:37.799 --> 28:40.052
HE COULD HAVE BEATEN ME

28:37.799 --> 28:40.052
DOWN THE STAIRS, I SUPPOSE.

28:40.093 --> 28:41.261
Stay with him.

28:41.303 --> 28:43.930
WHAT ARE YOU DOING, MAN?

28:41.303 --> 28:43.930
THERE'S CHICKS HERE.

28:43.972 --> 28:44.931
COME ON, NOW, GIRL.

28:44.973 --> 28:46.850
I'M ABOUT TIRED

28:44.973 --> 28:46.850
OF LOOKING FOR --

28:48.935 --> 28:50.812
HA! WHAT'S HAPPENING?

28:48.935 --> 28:50.812
THAT'S NICE.

28:50.854 --> 28:52.523
I LIKE THE CUT ON THAT.

28:50.854 --> 28:52.523
YOU --

28:52.565 --> 28:55.025
NO. OKAY.

28:55.067 --> 28:56.360
I'M NOT SUPPOSED

28:55.067 --> 28:56.360
TO BE HERE, HUH?

28:56.402 --> 28:57.403
MNH-MNH.

28:57.444 --> 29:00.573
RIGHT.

28:57.444 --> 29:00.573
YOU'RE NOT GONNA LET ME GO.

29:00.614 --> 29:02.658
MNH-MNH.

29:02.700 --> 29:05.160
THAT'S COOL. THAT'S COOL.

29:02.700 --> 29:05.160
I GOT AN INVITATION RIGHT HERE.

29:05.202 --> 29:07.787
MAN, THAT SUIT IS  GQ  SMOOTH.

29:05.202 --> 29:07.787
I LIKE THAT. YOU SHOULD DO THAT.

29:07.829 --> 29:09.122
IT'S...

29:09.164 --> 29:12.292
WHOO! DOWN!

29:09.164 --> 29:12.292
[ LAUGHS ]

29:14.545 --> 29:18.131
COME ON!

29:14.545 --> 29:18.131
I HATE THIS HOUSE!

29:23.762 --> 29:25.222
PARKER, WHERE ARE WE?

29:25.264 --> 29:27.391
SEE? I TOLD YOU

29:25.264 --> 29:27.391
THERE WAS SOMETHING WEIRD

29:27.433 --> 29:28.392
ABOUT THESE WALLS.

29:28.434 --> 29:29.602
WAIT, PAR--

29:29.643 --> 29:30.769
[ KNOCKING,

29:29.643 --> 29:30.769
PARTY MUSIC PLAYING FAINTLY ]

29:30.810 --> 29:32.688
PARKER, THE COMMS

29:30.810 --> 29:32.688
CAN'T GET THROUGH HERE,

29:32.730 --> 29:35.691
AND -- AND SECRET PASSAGE --

29:32.730 --> 29:35.691
WHAT, IS THAT MUSIC?

29:35.733 --> 29:37.526
OH, YOU HEAR THAT, TOO?

29:35.733 --> 29:37.526
OH.

29:37.568 --> 29:39.445
WE MUST BE UNDERNEATH

29:37.568 --> 29:39.445
THE PARTY.

29:39.486 --> 29:40.738
HEY, LOOK.

29:40.779 --> 29:43.031
OBVIOUSLY, I'M REAL HAPPY

29:40.779 --> 29:43.031
THAT YOU'RE OKAY, RIGHT?

29:43.073 --> 29:45.117
BUT YOU COULDN'T AT LEAST

29:43.073 --> 29:45.117
POP OUT, LET A BROTHER KNOW?

29:45.158 --> 29:46.785
I MEAN, WHAT WAS UP?

29:45.158 --> 29:46.785
WHAT WERE YOU DOING?

29:46.826 --> 29:48.078
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

29:48.120 --> 29:50.414
MORRIS BECK IS A VAMPIRE.

29:50.456 --> 29:51.749
SOMETIMES I WISH SOMEONE

29:51.790 --> 29:53.792
WOULD PUT A STAKE

29:51.790 --> 29:53.792
THROUGH HIS HEART.

29:53.833 --> 29:55.794
I'M NOT KIDDING.

29:55.835 --> 29:57.504
A REAL STAKE.

29:57.546 --> 29:59.423
[ CHUCKLES ]

29:59.465 --> 30:01.258
HEAR ENOUGH?

30:04.344 --> 30:07.514
[ THUNDER CRASHES ]

30:07.556 --> 30:08.932
[ FABRIC RIPS ]

30:08.974 --> 30:11.977
ELIOT, CHECK HIS JACKET

30:08.974 --> 30:11.977
FOR RIPS.

30:12.018 --> 30:14.229
I'M NOT GONNA LIE TO YOU, MAN.

30:14.271 --> 30:16.607
THIS IS GONNA HURT FOR A SECOND.

30:16.649 --> 30:18.191
WHAT IS?

30:20.068 --> 30:22.780
SORRY.

30:20.068 --> 30:22.780
I'M ADAPTING.

30:28.494 --> 30:30.370
THERE'S NO RIPS, NATE.

30:30.412 --> 30:32.038
NO RIPS.

30:32.080 --> 30:34.916
[ DOOR HINGES CREAK ]

30:34.958 --> 30:36.835
I FOUND PARKER, Y'ALL.

30:36.876 --> 30:38.337
AND WE GOT NEWS.

30:38.378 --> 30:41.923
YEAH. THIS HOUSE IS FULL

30:38.378 --> 30:41.923
OF SECRET PASSAGES.

30:41.965 --> 30:43.634
YOU JUST HAVE TO PULL

30:41.965 --> 30:43.634
ON A WALL LAMP.

30:43.676 --> 30:45.844
OH. AND WE FOUND THE SAFE

30:43.676 --> 30:45.844
AND THE BLUEPRINTS.

30:45.885 --> 30:47.513
SO WE ARE OFFICIALLY DONE.

30:47.554 --> 30:48.681
YEAH, I'M AFRAID NOT.

30:48.722 --> 30:49.973
BUT, YAY, PARKER'S BACK.

30:50.015 --> 30:51.475
THAT'S NOT EXACTLY GOOD NEWS.

30:51.517 --> 30:52.768
WHAT? WHY?

30:52.810 --> 30:54.936
THIS PROVES ANYBODY HERE

30:52.810 --> 30:54.936
COULD HAVE KILLED BECK.

30:54.978 --> 30:56.480
YEAH, THAT'S RIGHT,

30:54.978 --> 30:56.480
INCLUDING NATE.

30:56.522 --> 30:58.106
OKAY, QUIET, QUIET!

30:58.148 --> 30:59.650
Quiet, everybody.

30:58.148 --> 30:59.650
Quiet.

30:59.692 --> 31:01.485
Just...just...

31:01.527 --> 31:02.902
BE QUIET.

31:06.156 --> 31:07.949
GOODBYE, MY LITTLE FRIENDS.

31:07.991 --> 31:09.660
[ THUNDER CRASHES ]

31:15.415 --> 31:16.542
DAMN IT.

31:16.583 --> 31:18.293
WHAT IS IT?

31:16.583 --> 31:18.293
NO SIGNAL?

31:18.335 --> 31:20.003
NO. UM...

31:26.719 --> 31:29.137
I JUST WANTED TO GET YOU ALONE.

31:29.179 --> 31:30.764
[ CHUCKLES ]

31:29.179 --> 31:30.764
NICE THOUGHT.

31:30.806 --> 31:32.974
THOUGH TECHNICALLY,

31:30.806 --> 31:32.974
I'M STILL WORKING.

31:33.016 --> 31:35.060
BUT MAYBE I COULD MAKE

31:33.016 --> 31:35.060
AN EXCEPTION.

31:35.101 --> 31:37.396
DO YOU REALLY THINK

31:35.101 --> 31:37.396
I'M THIS STUPID?

31:37.437 --> 31:39.105
-I DON'T KNOW WHAT YOU MEAN.

31:37.437 --> 31:39.105
-NOTHING.

31:39.147 --> 31:40.273
JUST THAT PRETTY SURE

31:40.315 --> 31:42.150
YOU'VE BEEN LYING TO ME

31:40.315 --> 31:42.150
THIS WHOLE TIME.

31:42.192 --> 31:44.194
WHICH MEANS YOU'RE NOT AN

31:42.192 --> 31:44.194
ACTRESS TRYING TO KEEP HER GIG.

31:44.236 --> 31:46.613
WHICH MEANS YOU'RE IN ON IT.

31:46.655 --> 31:49.742
IN ON WHAT?

31:46.655 --> 31:49.742
RAY, I REALLY DON'T KNOW --

31:49.783 --> 31:51.451
YMA SUMAC WAS A SINGER

31:49.783 --> 31:51.451
IN THE '50s.

31:51.493 --> 31:53.662
"YMA" -- MIGHT WANT TO LEARN HOW

31:51.493 --> 31:53.662
TO PRONOUNCE IT.

31:53.704 --> 31:55.205
I LOOKED IT UP.

31:55.247 --> 31:56.998
ALONG WITH A COUPLE OF OTHER

31:55.247 --> 31:56.998
NAMES I THINK YOU MIGHT KNOW.

31:57.040 --> 31:59.376
WELL, YES, I...

31:59.418 --> 32:01.169
MY MUM WAS A REALLY BIG FAN.

32:01.211 --> 32:02.504
SAVE IT.

32:02.546 --> 32:05.048
I ALSO TOOK A PICTURE

32:02.546 --> 32:05.048
OF  MR.  GORDON...

32:05.090 --> 32:06.466
AND I SENT IT TO INTERPOL.

32:06.508 --> 32:08.343
THEY SAY HE'S A GUY

32:06.508 --> 32:08.343
NAMED NATHAN FORD.

32:08.385 --> 32:11.513
GRIFTER, THIEF, EX-CON...

32:11.555 --> 32:12.598
BAD GUY.

32:12.639 --> 32:14.850
YOU'VE GOT THIS ALL WRONG.

32:14.892 --> 32:19.855
I'VE NEVER HEARD OF THIS

32:14.892 --> 32:19.855
FORD PERSON IN MY ENTIRE LIFE.

32:19.897 --> 32:22.190
[ LAUGHS ]

32:22.232 --> 32:26.194
WOW, YOU'RE REALLY GOOD.

32:26.236 --> 32:29.072
NOW EXPLAIN TO ME WHY THERE WAS

32:26.236 --> 32:29.072
REAL BLOOD ON THE FLOOR...

32:29.114 --> 32:31.742
OR WHY YOU'RE TRYING TO STOP ME

32:29.114 --> 32:31.742
FROM SEEING BECK'S BODY.

32:33.952 --> 32:35.954
I NEVER SAW ANY BLOOD, RAY.

32:35.995 --> 32:38.916
MY MOTHER NAMED ME YMA

32:35.995 --> 32:38.916
AFTER HER FAVORITE SINGER.

32:38.957 --> 32:40.500
I'VE WORKED

32:38.957 --> 32:40.500
FOR MYSTERY INCORPORATED

32:40.542 --> 32:41.877
FOR ALL OF THREE WEEKS,

32:41.919 --> 32:46.005
AND I CAN'T BELIEVE

32:41.919 --> 32:46.005
YOU THINK I'M A KILLER.

32:47.382 --> 32:48.675
UGH.

32:48.717 --> 32:51.261
IT'S LIKE YOU REALLY BELIEVE

32:48.717 --> 32:51.261
WHAT YOU'RE SAYING.

32:55.724 --> 32:57.643
NOW, YOU'RE GONNA SIT HERE,

32:57.684 --> 33:00.312
YOU'RE GONNA BE QUIET...

33:00.353 --> 33:02.481
AND I'M GONNA GO DEAL

33:00.353 --> 33:02.481
WITH YOUR PARTNERS.

33:02.522 --> 33:04.483
[ SIGHS ]

33:04.524 --> 33:05.984
-NATE.

33:04.524 --> 33:05.984
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

33:06.025 --> 33:07.820
HAMMETT'S ON HIS WAY

33:06.025 --> 33:07.820
BACK TO YOU.

33:07.861 --> 33:09.988
Nate. Nate?!

33:10.029 --> 33:11.990
BUGGER!

33:25.879 --> 33:28.340
[ THUNDER CRASHES ]

33:37.975 --> 33:41.979
OKAY, GUYS. I GOT IT.

33:37.975 --> 33:41.979
I KNOW WHO KILLED MORRIS BECK.

33:42.020 --> 33:44.606
[ CLATTER ]

33:44.648 --> 33:45.816
OUT SO I CAN SEE YA.

33:45.858 --> 33:47.192
OKAY, OKAY.

33:45.858 --> 33:47.192
IT'S NOT WHAT IT LOOKS LIKE.

33:47.233 --> 33:49.110
IT LOOKS LIKE MORRIS BECK'S

33:47.233 --> 33:49.110
BEEN MURDERED.

33:49.152 --> 33:50.988
YOU'RE LEFT HOLDING THE BAG

33:49.152 --> 33:50.988
FOR IT.

33:51.029 --> 33:53.406
MAYBE IT  IS

33:51.029 --> 33:53.406
WHAT IT LOOKS LIKE.

33:53.448 --> 33:54.992
YOU KNOW YOUR RIGHTS, DON'T YOU?

33:55.033 --> 33:57.285
YEAH. YEAH. I-I DO.

33:55.033 --> 33:57.285
ABSOLUTELY I DO.

33:57.327 --> 34:00.038
BUT I DID NOT KILL HIM.

34:00.079 --> 34:01.289
I-I THINK I CAN TELL YOU

34:00.079 --> 34:01.289
WHO DID.

34:01.331 --> 34:03.375
GO AHEAD. I GOT NOTHING BUT TIME

34:01.331 --> 34:03.375
TILL MORNING.

34:03.416 --> 34:04.459
OKAY.

34:04.501 --> 34:06.252
WHO KILLED MORRIS BECK?

34:06.294 --> 34:09.130
WELL, BECK ARRIVES

34:06.294 --> 34:09.130
AT THE PARTY DRUNK.

34:09.172 --> 34:10.799
HE DOES THIS EVERY YEAR.

34:10.841 --> 34:13.510
GREETINGS, EVERYONE!

34:13.552 --> 34:14.803
YOU DON'T WANT TO BE IN BED

34:13.552 --> 34:14.803
WITH BECK.

34:14.845 --> 34:17.764
GUY LIKE THAT

34:14.845 --> 34:17.764
MAKES A  LOT  OF ENEMIES.

34:17.806 --> 34:19.641
YOU RIGGED THAT GAME, BECK.

34:19.683 --> 34:21.727
YOU KNOW IT, AND SO DO I.

34:21.768 --> 34:23.228
SOMETIMES I WISH SOMEBODY

34:23.269 --> 34:25.188
WOULD PUT A STAKE

34:23.269 --> 34:25.188
THROUGH HIS HEART.

34:25.230 --> 34:27.148
SO NOBODY LIKED THE GUY.

34:25.230 --> 34:27.148
SO WHAT?

34:27.190 --> 34:28.608
YEAH, SO, MOTIVE.

34:28.650 --> 34:30.318
I MEAN, EVERYONE IN THE HOUSE

34:28.650 --> 34:30.318
WAS AN ENEMY OF BECK'S.

34:30.360 --> 34:32.738
AND YOU'RE ENEMY NUMBER ONE,

34:30.360 --> 34:32.738
NATHAN FORD.

34:32.779 --> 34:34.280
EX-CONVICT.

34:34.322 --> 34:35.448
ARRESTED FIVE YEARS AGO

34:35.490 --> 34:37.325
FOR MAKING THREATS

34:35.490 --> 34:37.325
AGAINST HIS EMPLOYER,

34:37.367 --> 34:38.744
I.Y.S. INSURANCE.

34:38.785 --> 34:40.996
SOUNDS TO ME LIKE SOMEBODY'S

34:38.785 --> 34:40.996
GOT AN AX TO GRIND

34:41.038 --> 34:41.997
AGAINST A C.E.O.

34:42.039 --> 34:43.081
YOU KILLED HIM.

34:43.122 --> 34:44.332
BELIEVE ME, THERE ARE MOMENTS

34:44.374 --> 34:45.876
WHERE I DEFINITELY

34:44.374 --> 34:45.876
COULD SEE HIM DEAD.

34:45.918 --> 34:47.252
I WOULDN'T DO IT.

34:45.918 --> 34:47.252
SOMEONE WOULD.

34:47.293 --> 34:48.837
SOMEONE DID.

34:47.293 --> 34:48.837
SOMEONE DID IT IN THE DARK

34:48.879 --> 34:50.171
AND GOT AWAY FAST.

34:50.213 --> 34:53.466
ALL RIGHT, JUST FOR LAUGHS,

34:50.213 --> 34:53.466
WHERE DID THEY GO?

34:53.508 --> 34:55.761
SECRET PASSAGES.

34:58.597 --> 35:03.060
THEY RUN THROUGHOUT THE HOUSE.

35:04.895 --> 35:06.855
SEE, THE THING IS...

35:06.897 --> 35:11.192
WHOEVER DID THIS KNEW --

35:06.897 --> 35:11.192
KNEW THAT BECK WOULD BE DRUNK.

35:11.234 --> 35:14.112
AND HE GIVES HIS SPEECH

35:11.234 --> 35:14.112
ON THAT BALCONY EVERY YEAR.

35:14.153 --> 35:19.076
AT THE STROKE OF MIDNIGHT,

35:14.153 --> 35:19.076
SOMEONE  WILL DIE.

35:19.117 --> 35:21.620
AND ONE OF YOU IS THE KILLER.

35:21.661 --> 35:22.955
ONLY THIS YEAR,

35:22.996 --> 35:24.122
DURING A BLACKOUT,

35:24.163 --> 35:26.124
HE LOSES HIS BALANCE, HE FALLS.

35:26.165 --> 35:27.333
HE BREAKS HIS NECK.

35:27.375 --> 35:29.210
[ ELECTRICITY BUZZES ]

35:29.252 --> 35:30.670
TONIGHT WAS A MISTAKE.

35:30.712 --> 35:32.380
I'M NOT THERE, THIS THING PLAYS

35:30.712 --> 35:32.380
LIKE AN ACCIDENT.

35:32.422 --> 35:34.466
BUT YOU  WERE  THERE.

35:32.422 --> 35:34.466
EVERYBODY SAW YOU THERE.

35:34.507 --> 35:37.427
BUT THE STORM  WASN'T.

35:37.469 --> 35:39.387
SEE, THE BLACKOUTS --

35:39.429 --> 35:40.847
THEY ALWAYS FOLLOW THE LIGHTNING

35:40.889 --> 35:43.892
WHEN THE LIGHTNING STRIKES

35:40.889 --> 35:43.892
THE ISLAND'S POWER STATION.

35:43.934 --> 35:46.478
LIGHTNING, BLACKOUT,

35:43.934 --> 35:46.478
LIGHTNING...

35:46.519 --> 35:47.938
BLACKOUT.

35:47.980 --> 35:50.983
THIS TIME, IT WAS BLACKOUT...

35:51.024 --> 35:54.152
AND LIGHTNING AFTER.

35:54.193 --> 35:56.738
DID YOU KNOW THAT THERE'S

35:54.193 --> 35:56.738
A MASTER JUNCTION BOX

35:56.780 --> 35:58.239
IN THE PANTRY?

35:56.780 --> 35:58.239
THE KILLERS DID.

35:58.281 --> 35:59.699
THE  KILLERS.

35:59.741 --> 36:01.367
THE  KILLERS,  YES.

35:59.741 --> 36:01.367
THAT'S RIGHT -- THE KILLERS.

36:01.409 --> 36:02.410
THERE WERE TWO OF THEM.

36:02.452 --> 36:03.620
ONE WAS TO PULL

36:02.452 --> 36:03.620
THE MASTER SWITCH,

36:03.662 --> 36:04.997
THE OTHER WAS TO DO THE DEED.

36:05.038 --> 36:06.539
HEY, GET OUT!

36:06.581 --> 36:08.458
TWO KILLERS -- A TEAM.

36:08.500 --> 36:10.335
AND WHO ELSE KNEW

36:08.500 --> 36:10.335
ABOUT THESE PASSAGES?

36:10.376 --> 36:11.878
I DON'T THINK BECK WAS EXACTLY

36:11.920 --> 36:13.713
PRINTING THAT STUFF

36:11.920 --> 36:13.713
ON BUSINESS CARDS.

36:13.755 --> 36:14.798
WELL, I'LL TELL YA --

36:14.840 --> 36:17.216
BECK DEFINITELY,

36:14.840 --> 36:17.216
HIS ASSISTANT, MAYBE,

36:17.258 --> 36:20.512
SOME OF THE SECURITY STAFF,

36:17.258 --> 36:20.512
MR. CASE.

36:20.553 --> 36:22.514
OH, AND, UH, HIS DAUGHTER.

36:22.555 --> 36:24.099
YEAH. HIS DAUGHTER.

36:24.141 --> 36:25.934
YOU KNOW, SHE'S SPOILED.

36:24.141 --> 36:25.934
SHE'S RICH.

36:25.976 --> 36:27.060
IT'S TOTALED, OKAY?

36:27.102 --> 36:28.603
AND THE COPS ARE BEING

36:27.102 --> 36:28.603
TOTALLY FROSTY.

36:28.645 --> 36:30.105
AND I TOTALLY WASN'T DRUNK

36:28.645 --> 36:30.105
OR ANYTHING.

36:30.147 --> 36:31.356
DADDY NEEDS TO FIX.

36:31.397 --> 36:34.651
SHE'S A LOT SMARTER

36:31.397 --> 36:34.651
THAN MOST PEOPLE THINK.

36:34.693 --> 36:36.402
AND, YOU KNOW, SHE'S USED

36:34.693 --> 36:36.402
TO GETTING HER WAY,

36:36.444 --> 36:38.613
AND HER DAD IS IN

36:36.444 --> 36:38.613
THIS FINANCIAL BIND,

36:38.655 --> 36:39.823
YOU KNOW, WHAT WITH THE LAWSUITS

36:39.865 --> 36:41.533
AND THE UNION PROBLEMS

36:39.865 --> 36:41.533
AND ALL THAT STUFF.

36:41.574 --> 36:43.743
SO SHE'S TRYING TO GET HER HANDS

36:41.574 --> 36:43.743
ON THE FORTUNE

36:43.785 --> 36:45.745
BEFORE HE, DADDY,

36:43.785 --> 36:45.745
BLOWS THROUGH IT.

36:45.787 --> 36:49.041
SO SHE FINDS HERSELF A LUG.

36:45.787 --> 36:49.041
SHE SEDUCES THE LUG.

36:49.082 --> 36:50.375
SHE CONVINCES HIM

36:49.082 --> 36:50.375
THAT IT'D BE GREAT

36:50.416 --> 36:52.002
TO COME UP WITH THIS PLAN

36:50.416 --> 36:52.002
AND EVERYTHING

36:52.044 --> 36:53.294
AGAINST DEAR OLD DAD.

36:53.336 --> 36:54.671
THE LUG GOES FOR IT.

36:54.713 --> 36:57.132
SHE EVEN TELLS HIM

36:54.713 --> 36:57.132
THAT MAYBE EVEN AFTER ALL THIS,

36:57.174 --> 36:58.550
THEY COULD BE TOGETHER.

36:58.591 --> 37:01.469
SO, SHE SHOWS THE LUG THE SECRET

36:58.591 --> 37:01.469
PASSAGES AND EVERYTHING.

37:01.511 --> 37:04.097
SHE GOES TO THE KITCHEN,

37:01.511 --> 37:04.097
SHE PULLS THIS SWITCH,

37:04.139 --> 37:05.182
CREATES A BLACKOUT.

37:05.223 --> 37:06.808
THE LUG KILLS MORRIS BECK.

37:06.850 --> 37:09.144
I MEAN, THE WHOLE THING

37:06.850 --> 37:09.144
WAS JUST PERFECT.

37:09.186 --> 37:11.897
EXCEPT  YOU'RE  THERE.

37:11.938 --> 37:13.190
I...

37:15.525 --> 37:20.405
I  WAS  THERE,

37:15.525 --> 37:20.405
BUT  I  KNOW I DIDN'T DO IT.

37:20.446 --> 37:25.243
AND THE KILLERS --

37:20.446 --> 37:25.243
THEY  KNOW I DIDN'T DO IT.

37:25.284 --> 37:28.997
DETECTIVE,

37:25.284 --> 37:28.997
CAN I ASK YOU A QUESTION?

37:29.039 --> 37:32.709
MAY I PLEASE SEE YOUR BADGE?

37:37.630 --> 37:41.009
YOU SEE, I  WAS  THERE.

37:41.051 --> 37:44.846
AND I SAW THAT THE KILLER

37:41.051 --> 37:44.846
HAD INSIDE HIS JACKET

37:44.888 --> 37:47.807
A SHINY METAL OBJECT.

37:47.849 --> 37:50.894
IT WAS YOUR BADGE.

37:50.936 --> 37:52.854
YEAH. WELL...

37:52.896 --> 37:54.689
[ CHUCKLING ]

37:57.067 --> 38:00.361
I GOT TO HAND IT TO YOU.

37:57.067 --> 38:00.361
YOU REALLY GOT ME NAILED.

38:00.403 --> 38:02.197
WELL, I'M GLAD YOU AGREE.

38:02.239 --> 38:04.824
WHAT'S TO STOP ME

38:02.239 --> 38:04.824
FROM PLUGGING YOU RIGHT NOW?

38:04.866 --> 38:07.035
EVERYBODY SAW YOU THERE.

38:07.077 --> 38:08.870
ONCE THEY FIND OUT

38:07.077 --> 38:08.870
BECK'S CROAKED,

38:08.912 --> 38:10.914
WHO DO YOU THINK

38:08.912 --> 38:10.914
THEY'RE GONNA BELIEVE?

38:10.956 --> 38:12.707
YOU KNOW, YOU'RE RIGHT.

38:12.749 --> 38:15.961
IT'S -- IT'S A SAFE PLAY.

38:16.002 --> 38:18.463
JUST ONE PROBLEM.

38:18.504 --> 38:20.257
[ THUNDER CRASHES ]

38:20.298 --> 38:22.341
[ THUDDING ]

38:26.429 --> 38:28.014
LET'S GO!

38:28.056 --> 38:30.558
ELIOT, WE NEED THE GETAWAY NOW!

38:35.438 --> 38:37.857
[ GUNSHOTS ]

38:38.858 --> 38:41.236
RAY! WHAT THE HELL

38:38.858 --> 38:41.236
IS WITH THE SHOOTING?

38:41.278 --> 38:43.238
I SWEAR TO GOD,

38:41.278 --> 38:43.238
IF YOU MESS THIS UP --

38:43.280 --> 38:44.405
OH, DEAR.

38:44.447 --> 38:46.783
SOMEONE'S BEEN

38:44.447 --> 38:46.783
A VERY NAUGHTY GIRL.

38:50.078 --> 38:51.579
MISS SUMAC...

38:51.621 --> 38:55.750
PLEASE DON'T TELL ME THIS IS

38:51.621 --> 38:55.750
MORE OF YOUR "MYSTERY NIGHT."

38:55.792 --> 38:58.628
[ BREATHING DEEPLY ]

39:01.965 --> 39:03.300
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACH ]

39:07.137 --> 39:09.388
ALL RIGHT, FORD.

39:09.430 --> 39:12.017
I GOT ONE BULLET LEFT.

39:12.058 --> 39:14.060
IT'S GOT YOUR NAME ON IT.

39:14.102 --> 39:15.312
[ THUD ]

39:14.102 --> 39:15.312
-[ GRUNTS ]

39:19.732 --> 39:22.027
DO YOU KNOW HOW LONG IT TOOK ME

39:19.732 --> 39:22.027
TO HIDE THAT PIPE WRENCH

39:22.068 --> 39:23.069
IN THE LIBRARY?

39:24.946 --> 39:25.905
[ SIGHS ]

39:25.947 --> 39:28.283
[ DIALING ]

39:31.786 --> 39:34.122
DETECTIVE BONANNO?

39:34.164 --> 39:36.666
NATE FORD. YEAH.

39:36.708 --> 39:38.877
HAVE I GOT A STORY FOR YOU.

39:38.918 --> 39:40.461
